					<p>Nice explanation Martin! I have done something very similar in a ColorUtils for Java. I find it&#8217;s an interesting but very subjective matter and for many practical uses, you will want to seed the algorithm with avoidable colors.<br />
I attacked the problem looking at the color space as a HSV cone, placing points as far away from another in a 3D space (and often seeding the algorithm with the color black and white).</p>
